    <item>
      <title>Security Awareness Training Customized to Your Business</title>
      <link>https://www.cyberpilot.io/cyberpilot-blog/personalized-security-training-our-ai-customize-the-courses-for-your-company</link>
      <description>&lt;div class="hs-featured-image-wrapper"&gt; 
 &lt;a href="https://www.cyberpilot.io/cyberpilot-blog/personalized-security-training-our-ai-customize-the-courses-for-your-company" title="" class="hs-featured-image-link"&gt; &lt;img src="https://www.cyberpilot.io/hubfs/ChatGPT%20Image%2024.%20okt.%202025%2c%2015.41.55.png" alt="Generic gray courses than turns into color to the right as the get personalized" class="hs-featured-image" style="width:auto !important; max-width:50%; float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;"&gt; &lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;One size fits none&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Most people don’t fail security training because they don’t care, but because it feels irrelevant.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;A warehouse worker doesn’t see themselves in a phishing simulation about “Finance quarterly reports.”&lt;br&gt;A marketing manager doesn’t connect with password rules made for IT admins.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;And when something feels like it’s not made for you, you tune out.&lt;br&gt;That’s how risky behavior slips through the cracks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
