&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;One size fits none&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Most people don’t fail security training because they don’t care, but because it feels irrelevant.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;A warehouse worker doesn’t see themselves in a phishing simulation about “Finance quarterly reports.”&lt;br&gt;A marketing manager doesn’t connect with password rules made for IT admins.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;And when something feels like it’s not made for you, you tune out.&lt;br&gt;That’s how risky behavior slips through the cracks.&lt;/p&gt;  
